noun.description: A member of a North American people formerly living in eastern Wisconsin and now mainly in southern Wisconsin and Nebraska.
The Siouan language of the Winnebago.
A motor vehicle with living accommodations used when traveling long distances or camping.

adjective.description: Relating to the Winnebago people or their language.

origin: Algonquian, literally person of the dirty water, referring to the muddy Fox River.
